Class ControlPointPositionData

    • com.tractrac.clientmodule.details.Attachments

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<TimeObject>

    public class ControlPointPositionData
extends Position
    An instance of this class represents a position for a Control Point (or one of its two buoys/marks).

    The static method subscribe(com.tractrac.clientmodule.Event, com.tractrac.clientmodule.data.ICallbackData<com.tractrac.clientmodule.ControlPoint, com.tractrac.clientmodule.data.ControlPointPositionData>, long, long) can be used to receive positions.

    Custom data may be attached to each position instance.

    Version:
    2.0

    TracTrac

      • subscribe

        public static com.maptrack.client.io.TypeController subscribe(Event event,
                                              ICallbackData<ControlPoint,ControlPointPositionData> callback,
                                              long fromTime,
                                              long toTime)
        Subscribes to control point positions for a given Event.

        The method returns immediately and the positions are subsequently sent to a given callback, as they are received.

        The returned type controller should be added to a DataController.

        Parameters:
        event - the event from which to request the data.
        callback - the callback to receive the positions
        fromTime - stored positions (if supported) will be requested from this time
        toTime - stored positions (if supported) will be requested before this time
        Returns:
        the type controller
